Yes, on Stack Overflow you can filter the list of Active questions by how many days old they are. On the https://stackoverflow.com/questions page, select the **Active** tab, then use the date‑range filter (usually a dropdown labeled "All time", "Past week", "Past month", etc.) to limit the results to questions active within the last 7 days, 30 days, etc. This effectively filters Active questions by the number of days old. You can also achieve the same via URL parameters, e.g., adding `?sort=active&days=7` to show active questions from the past 7 days.


